1
00:00:01,360 --> 00:00:03,330
Only one more month until his release?

2
00:00:03,350 --> 00:00:04,850
His sentence was cut by four months?

3
00:00:05,360 --> 00:00:05,770
Yes.

4
00:00:06,550 --> 00:00:07,980
That's wonderful.

5
00:00:10,560 --> 00:00:11,890
When Yat-wai gets out,

6
00:00:12,270 --> 00:00:13,490
he's coming straight to my place.

7
00:00:13,750 --> 00:00:15,300
I'll make sure he eats well.

8
00:00:15,320 --> 00:00:16,620
He's skin and bones.

9
00:00:16,640 --> 00:00:18,260
I doubt they serve
anything decent in there.

10
00:00:18,710 --> 00:00:19,620
Youth is the time

11
00:00:19,640 --> 00:00:21,530
to lay the foundation
for lifelong health.

12
00:00:21,550 --> 00:00:23,300
Neglect it now, and regret may follow.

13
00:00:23,640 --> 00:00:24,780
Let's talk about this later.

14
00:00:25,800 --> 00:00:26,850
I'm serious.

15
00:00:28,640 --> 00:00:29,940
After Yat-wai comes out,

16
00:00:30,960 --> 00:00:32,050
I don't want him to live with you.

17
00:00:34,470 --> 00:00:36,540
I think you've really changed a lot.

18
00:00:37,520 --> 00:00:38,900
You weren't like this before.

19
00:00:39,350 --> 00:00:40,820
I don't know what happened.

20
00:00:40,840 --> 00:00:41,940
In the past six months,

21
00:00:41,960 --> 00:00:43,620
those major cases you judged

22
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:45,260
were truly horrifying.

23
00:00:46,350 --> 00:00:47,980
Look at Sek Chi-yeung's case.

24
00:00:48,790 --> 00:00:50,300
Everyone could see

25
00:00:50,320 --> 00:00:51,540
something was off with the witness.

26
00:00:52,600 --> 00:00:53,900
But rather than question it,

27
00:00:53,920 --> 00:00:55,260
you went straight to sentencing.

28
00:00:56,030 --> 00:00:56,650
Although

29
00:00:57,110 --> 00:00:58,410
you overturned it later,

30
00:00:58,750 --> 00:01:00,500
if you'd been clearer at the time,

31
00:01:00,880 --> 00:01:02,300
would an apology have been necessary?

32
00:01:04,400 --> 00:01:05,410
And the land deed case

33
00:01:05,920 --> 00:01:07,410
has caused such a stir.

34
00:01:08,200 --> 00:01:09,210
There was a hunger strike,

35
00:01:09,230 --> 00:01:10,490
and someone even got stabbed.

36
00:01:11,400 --> 00:01:11,930
Although

37
00:01:12,120 --> 00:01:12,980
that land deed

38
00:01:13,230 --> 00:01:14,660
might have been illegal,

39
00:01:15,150 --> 00:01:16,570
what the law upholds

40
00:01:16,840 --> 00:01:18,050
is not just the letter of the law.

41
00:01:18,400 --> 00:01:19,570
Humanity and justice

42
00:01:19,590 --> 00:01:21,260
must also exist.

43
00:01:21,680 --> 00:01:23,100
Do you think we can rely on

44
00:01:23,120 --> 00:01:24,260
humanity and justice

45
00:01:24,590 --> 00:01:25,980
to file an appeal?

46
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:26,980
Of course we can.

47
00:01:28,310 --> 00:01:29,290
Then I'll leave it to you.

48
00:01:30,120 --> 00:01:31,020
Me?

49
00:02:56,630 --> 00:03:02,280
[Justice Is Mine]

50
00:03:02,780 --> 00:03:05,380
[Episode 19]

51
00:03:07,620 --> 00:03:09,020
The injured is now in the ICU.

52
00:03:09,300 --> 00:03:11,220
The tetanus infection
has spread to his internal organs.

53
00:03:11,580 --> 00:03:12,860
His condition is critical.

54
00:03:12,980 --> 00:03:14,700
This is all the fault
of those shameless developers.

55
00:03:14,700 --> 00:03:15,860
Who do they think they are,
blocking my path

56
00:03:15,860 --> 00:03:16,780
and putting up fences like that?

57
00:03:16,780 --> 00:03:18,180
That's not a reason for you
to hurt someone.

58
00:03:18,180 --> 00:03:19,140
I didn't.

59
00:03:19,140 --> 00:03:20,780
I just wanted to take down the fences.

60
00:03:21,220 --> 00:03:22,620
You were holding a very sharp,

61
00:03:22,620 --> 00:03:23,980
rusty weapon

62
00:03:24,180 --> 00:03:25,420
that could have taken someone's life
at any moment.

63
00:03:25,420 --> 00:03:27,020
Cheung-kwai gave it to me.

64
00:03:27,900 --> 00:03:28,540
Is that so?

65
00:03:29,420 --> 00:03:30,740
I just grabbed it

66
00:03:31,260 --> 00:03:32,460
from his house.

67
00:03:32,740 --> 00:03:33,260
Hey,

68
00:03:33,740 --> 00:03:34,980
we were there to tear down fences,

69
00:03:34,980 --> 00:03:36,020
not take lives.

70
00:03:36,180 --> 00:03:37,660
This is resistance against power

71
00:03:37,660 --> 00:03:38,460
and those shameless developers.

72
00:03:38,460 --> 00:03:39,340
Shut up.

73
00:03:40,780 --> 00:03:41,660
Drop the nonsense.

74
00:03:42,660 --> 00:03:43,620
Chui Dai-ngau said

75
00:03:43,980 --> 00:03:45,420
he was at the back,

76
00:03:45,940 --> 00:03:47,380
got pushed forward suddenly,

77
00:03:47,740 --> 00:03:48,860
and ended up hurting the guy
by accident.

78
00:03:49,740 --> 00:03:51,020
There was so much chaos at the time.

79
00:03:51,300 --> 00:03:52,820
I got pushed too, Madam.

80
00:03:53,420 --> 00:03:54,980
In such chaos,

81
00:03:55,260 --> 00:03:56,900
you could still tell which one

82
00:03:57,100 --> 00:03:58,380
was sharp enough to hurt someone

83
00:03:58,940 --> 00:03:59,820
and

84
00:04:00,500 --> 00:04:01,500
which wasn't?

85
00:04:11,300 --> 00:04:12,260
Is that a new rule?

86
00:04:12,860 --> 00:04:14,020
So now, even as the boss,

87
00:04:14,020 --> 00:04:15,740
I don't get any private space?

88
00:04:24,700 --> 00:04:25,820
Alright, I give up.

89
00:04:25,820 --> 00:04:26,380
Go ahead.

90
00:04:27,940 --> 00:04:29,340
What's left to say?

91
00:04:29,660 --> 00:04:30,540
The real culprit

92
00:04:30,540 --> 00:04:32,260
struts out of the station,

93
00:04:32,580 --> 00:04:33,460
and this fool

94
00:04:33,660 --> 00:04:35,060
takes the blame

95
00:04:35,340 --> 00:04:36,820
and gets charged.

96
00:04:37,180 --> 00:04:38,620
Chi Cheung-kwai was released?

97
00:04:38,620 --> 00:04:39,540
Of course he was.

98
00:04:39,540 --> 00:04:40,540
There wasn't enough evidence.

99
00:04:40,820 --> 00:04:41,700
What else could we do,

100
00:04:41,700 --> 00:04:42,460
keep him locked up?

101
00:04:43,100 --> 00:04:44,300
No matter what,

102
00:04:44,740 --> 00:04:45,740
the fact remains

103
00:04:45,740 --> 00:04:47,020
that someone

104
00:04:47,020 --> 00:04:48,300
was seriously injured.

105
00:04:48,940 --> 00:04:50,020
As a police officer,

106
00:04:50,340 --> 00:04:51,300
you must enforce the law.

107
00:04:58,140 --> 00:04:58,540
You...

108
00:05:04,940 --> 00:05:05,540
Uncle,

109
00:05:05,740 --> 00:05:07,220
I know how much you enjoy tea,

110
00:05:07,660 --> 00:05:09,220
so I had someone

111
00:05:09,380 --> 00:05:11,340
bring back a cake
of aged Pu'er tea just for you.

112
00:05:13,980 --> 00:05:15,300
Take your time with the tea.

113
00:05:15,540 --> 00:05:16,740
I think everyone's heard

114
00:05:17,260 --> 00:05:18,740
Dai-ngau was arrested.

115
00:05:19,540 --> 00:05:20,220
And Mr. Tsang

116
00:05:20,580 --> 00:05:21,940
is in the hospital on a hunger strike.

117
00:05:22,460 --> 00:05:24,580
So Uncle said...

118
00:05:24,700 --> 00:05:25,700
Never mind.

119
00:05:26,500 --> 00:05:27,420
I'll sell the land.

120
00:05:29,420 --> 00:05:30,060
You sure?

121
00:05:30,260 --> 00:05:30,940
Yes.

122
00:05:33,140 --> 00:05:34,180
Seriously?

123
00:05:34,180 --> 00:05:35,180
How can this be okay?

124
00:05:37,500 --> 00:05:38,620
What else can he do?

125
00:05:39,580 --> 00:05:40,740
It's the way things are going.

126
00:05:41,340 --> 00:05:43,420
The redevelopment of the old town

127
00:05:44,220 --> 00:05:46,500
could be a good thing down the line.

128
00:05:47,140 --> 00:05:47,740
Cheung-wing,

129
00:05:47,740 --> 00:05:49,500
you represent everyone to negotiate.

130
00:05:50,060 --> 00:05:52,220
Most importantly, there must be
a like-for-like replacement.

131
00:05:52,380 --> 00:05:53,700
No cutting corners

132
00:05:53,900 --> 00:05:55,220
on compensation.

133
00:05:56,100 --> 00:05:57,500
If this can be settled,

134
00:05:57,740 --> 00:05:58,220
Cheung-wing,

135
00:05:58,220 --> 00:06:00,180
you'll be the hero of the old town.

136
00:06:00,380 --> 00:06:00,860
No.

137
00:06:01,340 --> 00:06:01,940
Come on,

138
00:06:02,300 --> 00:06:03,340
let me toast you

139
00:06:03,580 --> 00:06:04,220
with tea.

140
00:06:04,420 --> 00:06:04,740
Come on.

141
00:06:04,740 --> 00:06:05,700
I don't deserve it.

142
00:06:05,700 --> 00:06:06,220
Uncle,

143
00:06:06,620 --> 00:06:07,820
this is what I should do.

144
00:06:08,740 --> 00:06:09,220
Enjoy the tea.

145
00:06:09,220 --> 00:06:09,540
Okay.

146
00:06:09,540 --> 00:06:10,180
Uncle, have some tea.

147
00:06:10,180 --> 00:06:10,700
Okay.

148
00:06:10,700 --> 00:06:11,500
Everyone, help yourselves.

149
00:06:14,060 --> 00:06:14,500
Cheung-wing,

150
00:06:14,860 --> 00:06:15,780
you're something else

151
00:06:16,420 --> 00:06:17,180
for making Dai-ngau

152
00:06:17,180 --> 00:06:18,700
into a game-changer.

153
00:06:19,820 --> 00:06:20,660
Cut it out.

154
00:06:20,900 --> 00:06:21,980
You played your part too.

155
00:06:22,140 --> 00:06:23,220
You'll get your share. Don't worry.

156
00:06:23,220 --> 00:06:24,180
Of course.

157
00:06:24,340 --> 00:06:25,620
I risked my life for this.

158
00:06:26,220 --> 00:06:27,660
Then why are you still hanging around?

159
00:06:28,380 --> 00:06:29,740
Go make sure everything's under control.

160
00:06:30,340 --> 00:06:30,940
Understood.

161
00:06:32,180 --> 00:06:32,940
Ow!

162
00:06:33,460 --> 00:06:34,300
Cheung-wing.

163
00:06:36,540 --> 00:06:37,220
Mr. Yuen,

164
00:06:38,060 --> 00:06:38,900
do you need something from me?

165
00:06:39,660 --> 00:06:41,300
Since you're close with the chairman,

166
00:06:41,300 --> 00:06:43,460
could you ask him
about selling the house for me?

167
00:06:45,380 --> 00:06:46,700
Selling the house?

168
00:06:46,860 --> 00:06:48,020
Everyone's taking the deal,

169
00:06:48,020 --> 00:06:48,900
and you going for it too?

170
00:06:49,220 --> 00:06:50,380
Our house

171
00:06:50,380 --> 00:06:52,460
was bought when Wai and Sa got married.

172
00:06:52,860 --> 00:06:54,220
It was under her name.

173
00:06:54,820 --> 00:06:56,060
With Wai gone

174
00:06:56,340 --> 00:06:57,900
and Sa working far away

175
00:06:57,900 --> 00:06:58,820
with the kids,

176
00:06:59,180 --> 00:07:00,180
she can't get back here to sign.

177
00:07:00,460 --> 00:07:02,060
We want to sell, but we're blocked.

178
00:07:03,380 --> 00:07:04,100
That's simple.

179
00:07:04,580 --> 00:07:06,460
Just write a letter of authorization.

180
00:07:07,060 --> 00:07:08,100
Can that really work?

181
00:07:08,260 --> 00:07:09,140
Of course it can.

182
00:07:10,620 --> 00:07:11,100
Chi.

183
00:07:25,820 --> 00:07:26,740
Come on, get in there.

184
00:07:26,940 --> 00:07:27,580
Back to your room.

185
00:07:30,060 --> 00:07:32,020
Are you really going to avoid me
like I'm the plague?

186
00:07:34,540 --> 00:07:36,340
After I agreed to let you stay
with your kids,

187
00:07:36,340 --> 00:07:36,980
the least you could do is say thanks

188
00:07:36,980 --> 00:07:38,340
instead of walking around
looking so miserable.

189
00:07:41,060 --> 00:07:41,500
Come here.

190
00:07:46,740 --> 00:07:47,860
I told you to come here!

191
00:07:58,220 --> 00:07:58,860
Sign this.

192
00:07:59,820 --> 00:08:00,500
What is it?

193
00:08:01,380 --> 00:08:02,540
Good stuff.

194
00:08:03,380 --> 00:08:04,620
The old town

195
00:08:05,020 --> 00:08:06,740
is being redeveloped.

196
00:08:07,340 --> 00:08:09,020
This letter gets you a new house
and compensation.

197
00:08:09,660 --> 00:08:10,500
It's for the house under your name,

198
00:08:10,500 --> 00:08:11,940
where your parents live.

199
00:08:12,500 --> 00:08:13,740
I need your signature to authorize it.

200
00:08:15,060 --> 00:08:16,460
Let me see my parents.

201
00:08:17,260 --> 00:08:20,300
I let you call them once a month,
just so they know you're okay.

202
00:08:21,260 --> 00:08:23,140
I'm just trying to do some good

203
00:08:23,140 --> 00:08:24,100
and rack up a bit of karma.

204
00:08:24,580 --> 00:08:25,820
Don't push your luck.

205
00:08:25,820 --> 00:08:26,780
Don't force me

206
00:08:26,780 --> 00:08:28,420
take your kids away.

207
00:08:50,460 --> 00:08:51,780
When will you let me go?

208
00:08:54,540 --> 00:08:55,540
Depends on my mood.

209
00:09:05,420 --> 00:09:06,740
Behave yourself,

210
00:09:07,540 --> 00:09:08,460
and you can leave anytime.

211
00:09:26,020 --> 00:09:27,340
The land acquisition's done,

212
00:09:27,780 --> 00:09:29,660
and the redevelopment

213
00:09:29,980 --> 00:09:31,180
of the old town is finally underway.

214
00:09:31,780 --> 00:09:33,660
Thanks to both of you
for your strong support.

215
00:09:34,620 --> 00:09:35,300
Thank you.

216
00:09:36,100 --> 00:09:37,340
Don't just say thank you.

217
00:09:37,740 --> 00:09:39,100
Most importantly,

218
00:09:39,100 --> 00:09:40,780
don't forget to cut me in.

219
00:09:41,100 --> 00:09:42,940
I pulled off a classic bait-and-switch.

220
00:09:42,940 --> 00:09:44,060
If it weren't for me,

221
00:09:44,060 --> 00:09:45,340
legal land acquisition

222
00:09:45,340 --> 00:09:46,500
would be out of the question.

223
00:09:47,140 --> 00:09:48,780
If no one held the judge's son hostage

224
00:09:48,780 --> 00:09:49,500
as leverage,

225
00:09:49,940 --> 00:09:51,660
what could a mere piece of paper do?

226
00:09:53,940 --> 00:09:55,580
Anyway, both of you are heroes.

227
00:09:55,740 --> 00:09:57,060
We'll split any profits

228
00:09:57,060 --> 00:09:58,220
down the line.

229
00:09:59,260 --> 00:10:01,100
My part is done.

230
00:10:01,500 --> 00:10:02,860
The rest of it

231
00:10:03,540 --> 00:10:04,900
is now up to you, Mr. Hon Lit.

232
00:10:08,060 --> 00:10:09,260
I heard the judge's son

233
00:10:09,660 --> 00:10:10,780
will be released early.

234
00:10:11,940 --> 00:10:13,620
He'll be out sooner or later.

235
00:10:14,140 --> 00:10:15,540
Just think of it as tossing him a bone.

236
00:10:16,700 --> 00:10:18,060
Land acquisition's done.

237
00:10:18,060 --> 00:10:19,100
Construction's officially underway.

238
00:10:19,420 --> 00:10:20,060
My mission

239
00:10:20,580 --> 00:10:21,500
is complete.

240
00:10:22,540 --> 00:10:24,020
Then do whatever you want.

241
00:10:24,580 --> 00:10:25,780
I'm not getting involved anymore.

242
00:10:28,780 --> 00:10:29,420
Come on,

243
00:10:29,660 --> 00:10:30,300
have some while it's nice and warm.

244
00:10:30,700 --> 00:10:31,580
Okay, thank you.

245
00:10:33,900 --> 00:10:34,620
Have a shrimp.

246
00:10:44,660 --> 00:10:45,220
Yat-wai,

247
00:10:46,180 --> 00:10:46,860
how come

248
00:10:47,260 --> 00:10:48,540
you're looking skinnier?

249
00:10:51,940 --> 00:10:52,980
Pretty much the same as before.

250
00:10:55,420 --> 00:10:56,340
Have you been studying?

251
00:10:57,020 --> 00:10:58,220
You'll be out soon.

252
00:10:58,700 --> 00:10:59,580
Grandma said

253
00:10:59,900 --> 00:11:01,380
she's getting you lots of good food

254
00:11:01,420 --> 00:11:02,260
to fatten you up.

255
00:11:04,580 --> 00:11:05,100
Dad,

256
00:11:06,180 --> 00:11:06,980
actually,

257
00:11:07,660 --> 00:11:09,180
I'm okay with not getting out early.

258
00:11:10,500 --> 00:11:11,180
What did you say?

259
00:11:11,780 --> 00:11:12,900
There are only a few months left.

260
00:11:13,580 --> 00:11:14,220
I can manage it.

261
00:11:15,540 --> 00:11:15,980
Are you saying...?

262
00:11:16,020 --> 00:11:16,500
Dad,

263
00:11:17,780 --> 00:11:18,420
I used to

264
00:11:19,300 --> 00:11:20,700
watch you, in your judge's robe,

265
00:11:21,380 --> 00:11:22,540
presiding over cases in court.

266
00:11:23,380 --> 00:11:24,060
It was so cool.

267
00:11:25,540 --> 00:11:27,420
I wonder if I'll ever get to
see that again.

268
00:11:30,820 --> 00:11:31,780
Of course.

269
00:11:33,580 --> 00:11:34,980
I'll take you home soon.

270
00:11:36,140 --> 00:11:36,980
Just hold on a bit longer, okay?

271
00:11:42,780 --> 00:11:43,780
[SH Asset Holdings Limited]
Out with the old,

272
00:11:44,020 --> 00:11:45,020
in with the new.

273
00:11:45,900 --> 00:11:47,780
Society keeps moving forward.

274
00:11:48,420 --> 00:11:48,860
Therefore,

275
00:11:49,540 --> 00:11:50,940
the old town's future

276
00:11:51,300 --> 00:11:53,020
will only get better.

277
00:11:53,180 --> 00:11:53,620
Well said!

278
00:11:53,660 --> 00:11:55,300
- Bravo!
- Great!

279
00:11:55,500 --> 00:11:55,940
Well said!

280
00:11:57,580 --> 00:11:58,420
Mr. Chung,

281
00:11:59,060 --> 00:12:00,300
that's not quite right.

282
00:12:01,180 --> 00:12:03,100
Sure, development is the way forward,

283
00:12:03,500 --> 00:12:04,380
but old things

284
00:12:04,420 --> 00:12:05,620
carry historical value too.

285
00:12:06,380 --> 00:12:07,780
On behalf of the residents
of the old town,

286
00:12:08,180 --> 00:12:09,900
we hope you can preserve
Tai Wong Temple.

287
00:12:10,060 --> 00:12:10,820
That's impossible.

288
00:12:11,780 --> 00:12:13,300
In our plan,

289
00:12:13,820 --> 00:12:14,900
all buildings in this area

290
00:12:14,900 --> 00:12:16,740
must be razed to the ground.

291
00:12:18,820 --> 00:12:19,500
Who says you can do that?

292
00:12:21,300 --> 00:12:22,060
How can this be?

293
00:12:22,060 --> 00:12:22,700
This is too much.

294
00:12:22,700 --> 00:12:23,140
Uncle is here.

295
00:12:23,180 --> 00:12:23,860
What gives you the right?

296
00:12:23,900 --> 00:12:24,780
Uncle!

297
00:12:24,780 --> 00:12:26,300
- Uncle!
- Uncle!

298
00:12:26,300 --> 00:12:27,020
Uncle is here!

299
00:12:27,020 --> 00:12:28,540
I think preserving Tai Wong Temple

300
00:12:28,900 --> 00:12:30,020
is entirely possible.

301
00:12:31,060 --> 00:12:32,140
I'm Chow Lok-man,

302
00:12:32,460 --> 00:12:34,180
Uncle Chen's appointed lawyer.

303
00:12:34,540 --> 00:12:35,940
I've already represented the old town

304
00:12:36,260 --> 00:12:37,380
on procedural justice grounds

305
00:12:37,980 --> 00:12:39,500
and filed for a court injunction.

306
00:12:43,820 --> 00:12:45,100
I really

307
00:12:45,100 --> 00:12:46,740
let everyone down

308
00:12:46,740 --> 00:12:48,580
for failing to protect our home.

309
00:12:48,580 --> 00:12:50,300
But the tides have turned

310
00:12:50,660 --> 00:12:52,020
in the land acquisition.

311
00:12:52,020 --> 00:12:53,700
I hope that everyone

312
00:12:53,700 --> 00:12:55,220
will continue to stand by me.

313
00:12:55,220 --> 00:12:56,420
- Great!
- Splendid!

314
00:12:56,420 --> 00:12:59,940
- Uncle, you have our support!
- We're with you!

315
00:13:00,700 --> 00:13:01,460
Uncle, we've got your back!

316
00:13:01,460 --> 00:13:02,900
Take care of what needs doing.

317
00:13:03,580 --> 00:13:04,340
We'll always stand by you!

318
00:13:04,740 --> 00:13:05,780
Uncle, we're behind you!

319
00:13:06,100 --> 00:13:08,300
- We're here for you!
- We're all with you, Uncle!

320
00:13:13,060 --> 00:13:13,780
What do you mean?

321
00:13:13,900 --> 00:13:15,900
[The old town sues the developer again
for violating procedural justice]

322
00:13:22,620 --> 00:13:23,780
Procedural justice

323
00:13:24,260 --> 00:13:26,540
can only be invoked
if it involves public interest.

324
00:13:27,260 --> 00:13:28,060
It's very regrettable

325
00:13:28,300 --> 00:13:30,340
that they actually found grounds
for appeal.

326
00:13:31,740 --> 00:13:33,100
Wasn't this lawyer, Chow,

327
00:13:33,300 --> 00:13:34,740
your student once?

328
00:13:34,980 --> 00:13:35,500
Yes.

329
00:13:36,420 --> 00:13:38,220
The student going up against her master,

330
00:13:38,700 --> 00:13:39,420
like a duel, huh?

331
00:13:40,260 --> 00:13:41,380
I'd do the same if I were her.

332
00:13:41,820 --> 00:13:43,140
If I win, people will know my name.

333
00:13:43,420 --> 00:13:44,140
If I lose,

334
00:13:44,140 --> 00:13:45,340
well, it's just losing to my master.

335
00:13:46,020 --> 00:13:48,180
So what are your chances of winning?

336
00:13:51,220 --> 00:13:52,060
Don't worry.

337
00:13:52,420 --> 00:13:53,700
They don't have new evidence.

338
00:13:54,140 --> 00:13:56,060
The appeal is just a process.

339
00:13:56,300 --> 00:13:57,380
You don't need to worry so much.

340
00:13:57,780 --> 00:13:58,980
When will the retrial be?

341
00:13:59,300 --> 00:14:00,620
The abrupt halt in progress

342
00:14:00,620 --> 00:14:02,460
will result in major losses
for the developer.

343
00:14:03,140 --> 00:14:04,020
My estimate

344
00:14:04,020 --> 00:14:05,220
is around one week.

345
00:14:08,540 --> 00:14:09,140
Don't worry.

346
00:14:09,540 --> 00:14:10,740
I've been in a pretty good mood lately,

347
00:14:11,180 --> 00:14:12,580
and my rulings have gone really well.

348
00:14:13,260 --> 00:14:14,340
Why the high spirit?

349
00:14:14,900 --> 00:14:15,660
My son

350
00:14:15,660 --> 00:14:16,820
can be let out ahead of schedule.

351
00:14:16,820 --> 00:14:17,380
Don't you remember?

352
00:14:19,140 --> 00:14:19,900
I do.

353
00:14:21,020 --> 00:14:22,180
Winning the case

354
00:14:22,660 --> 00:14:24,260
and your son walking free

355
00:14:24,420 --> 00:14:25,580
is a double blessing.

356
00:14:25,580 --> 00:14:26,220
Exactly.

357
00:14:26,620 --> 00:14:27,980
My son's release,

358
00:14:27,980 --> 00:14:29,460
and the verdict goes your way.

359
00:14:29,980 --> 00:14:31,820
Two joys at once.

360
00:14:35,380 --> 00:14:37,540
[Hokong Judiciary]

361
00:14:45,900 --> 00:14:47,100
You got a new car.

362
00:14:51,140 --> 00:14:51,660
Lok-man.

363
00:14:58,700 --> 00:15:00,220
I won't tell you anything.

364
00:15:00,740 --> 00:15:02,180
And don't try or intend

365
00:15:02,620 --> 00:15:03,780
to tell me how to do my job.

366
00:15:07,540 --> 00:15:09,180
Your bag's still open.

367
00:15:25,940 --> 00:15:27,140
Land disputes

368
00:15:27,140 --> 00:15:28,500
belong to the civil domain.

369
00:15:28,940 --> 00:15:30,580
As both the prosecution
and defense are present,

370
00:15:30,740 --> 00:15:32,420
you may engage
in dialog and negotiation

371
00:15:32,420 --> 00:15:33,260
to settle the matter.

372
00:15:33,860 --> 00:15:35,900
The only condition my client can accept

373
00:15:36,260 --> 00:15:37,420
is that the developer

374
00:15:37,420 --> 00:15:39,740
must respect
the old town's land ownership.

375
00:15:40,460 --> 00:15:41,500
Only then can both sides

376
00:15:41,500 --> 00:15:42,940
have room for a settlement.

377
00:15:43,300 --> 00:15:45,380
The court has declared
the land deed to be forged.

378
00:15:45,820 --> 00:15:47,740
Therefore, land ownership
does not exist.

379
00:15:48,020 --> 00:15:49,460
The land must be returned
to the government,

380
00:15:49,460 --> 00:15:50,860
and then developed by the developer.

381
00:15:52,020 --> 00:15:53,180
We respect the law,

382
00:15:53,540 --> 00:15:54,340
and at the same time,

383
00:15:54,660 --> 00:15:56,500
we respect the historical significance
of the land

384
00:15:56,860 --> 00:15:58,940
and indigenous residents
who have preserved its legacy

385
00:15:59,220 --> 00:16:01,300
by living here for centuries.

386
00:16:01,300 --> 00:16:01,940
Prosecution counsel,

387
00:16:02,500 --> 00:16:04,100
can history put food on the table?

388
00:16:04,980 --> 00:16:06,140
Moreover,

389
00:16:06,460 --> 00:16:07,620
what's true doesn't change,

390
00:16:08,300 --> 00:16:08,980
and what's false

391
00:16:09,340 --> 00:16:10,020
can't be made true.

392
00:16:11,420 --> 00:16:12,860
My land deed is real.

393
00:16:13,300 --> 00:16:14,060
Your Honor,

394
00:16:14,420 --> 00:16:15,740
it's as real as it gets!

395
00:16:16,900 --> 00:16:17,740
Prosecution counsel,

396
00:16:18,220 --> 00:16:19,500
remind your client

397
00:16:19,500 --> 00:16:20,460
to remain calm.

398
00:16:21,140 --> 00:16:21,820
Calm down.

399
00:16:23,140 --> 00:16:24,860
The prosecution has raised concerns

400
00:16:25,100 --> 00:16:26,820
regarding Identification Report No. 8

401
00:16:26,820 --> 00:16:27,660
from the initial trial.

402
00:16:28,380 --> 00:16:29,620
We respectfully request that the court

403
00:16:29,620 --> 00:16:31,020
authorize a re-evaluation

404
00:16:31,020 --> 00:16:32,260
of this critical piece of evidence.

405
00:16:32,620 --> 00:16:33,300
Objection.

406
00:16:33,580 --> 00:16:35,500
The identification was performed

407
00:16:35,500 --> 00:16:36,300
using the most advanced tools available.

408
00:16:36,300 --> 00:16:37,780
No matter how many times it's done,

409
00:16:38,220 --> 00:16:38,860
the result

410
00:16:39,340 --> 00:16:40,300
won't change.

411
00:16:40,660 --> 00:16:41,300
The outcome

412
00:16:41,660 --> 00:16:43,060
bears on public interest.

413
00:16:43,260 --> 00:16:45,020
Denying a re-evaluation

414
00:16:45,020 --> 00:16:46,460
would constitute
a breach of procedural justice.

415
00:16:47,020 --> 00:16:47,940
This forms the basis

416
00:16:47,940 --> 00:16:48,820
of my client's appeal.

417
00:16:48,820 --> 00:16:49,660
Objection.

418
00:16:49,660 --> 00:16:51,140
Further delay serves no purpose.

419
00:16:57,060 --> 00:16:58,380
The Court finds
the prosecution's grounds

420
00:16:58,380 --> 00:16:59,660
for appeal to be valid.

421
00:17:00,300 --> 00:17:01,020
This case

422
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:02,460
will be retried

423
00:17:02,460 --> 00:17:03,340
in one week.

424
00:17:12,740 --> 00:17:13,620
Congratulations

425
00:17:13,820 --> 00:17:15,380
on successfully filing your appeal

426
00:17:15,380 --> 00:17:16,140
in the land case.

427
00:17:17,060 --> 00:17:18,740
I'm not good
at these kinds of cases at all.

428
00:17:18,980 --> 00:17:20,260
Thank you for reminding me

429
00:17:20,260 --> 00:17:22,060
that I could appeal
based on procedural justice.

430
00:17:23,140 --> 00:17:25,140
As you gain more experience,

431
00:17:25,380 --> 00:17:27,100
you'll find no case too challenging.

432
00:17:33,300 --> 00:17:34,660
I still don't quite understand

433
00:17:35,860 --> 00:17:36,660
why

434
00:17:37,260 --> 00:17:38,300
you came to me.

435
00:17:39,180 --> 00:17:40,140
I mean,

436
00:17:40,860 --> 00:17:42,740
why did you ask me to do this?

437
00:17:45,060 --> 00:17:46,340
Although I'm retired,

438
00:17:46,860 --> 00:17:48,580
I am still a judge.

439
00:17:49,460 --> 00:17:51,060
The commitment to justice

440
00:17:51,660 --> 00:17:53,060
has always been part of who I am.

441
00:17:53,900 --> 00:17:55,260
I just did

442
00:17:55,260 --> 00:17:56,140
what I ought to do.

443
00:17:57,300 --> 00:17:58,980
Not every judge is like you.

444
00:17:59,700 --> 00:18:00,220
Mr. Chun,

445
00:18:00,860 --> 00:18:02,020
for one, definitely isn't.

446
00:18:05,260 --> 00:18:06,820
It's precisely because
he is the opponent.

447
00:18:07,380 --> 00:18:08,300
You know,

448
00:18:08,700 --> 00:18:09,980
many lawyers

449
00:18:09,980 --> 00:18:11,380
wouldn't risk offending

450
00:18:11,380 --> 00:18:12,620
a court president.

451
00:18:13,180 --> 00:18:14,020
But you've got the guts.

452
00:18:14,460 --> 00:18:16,060
That's why I came to you.

453
00:18:17,820 --> 00:18:19,020
I'm happy to take part in cracking down

454
00:18:19,180 --> 00:18:20,180
on shady ties between officials
and business interests.

455
00:18:22,100 --> 00:18:23,460
Seems I choose the right person.

456
00:18:32,060 --> 00:18:32,500
Hello?

457
00:18:32,860 --> 00:18:33,380
Chun Yue.

458
00:18:34,180 --> 00:18:34,700
Help me.

459
00:18:35,460 --> 00:18:36,180
Mrs. Cho?

460
00:18:36,660 --> 00:18:38,060
Hello?

461
00:18:48,740 --> 00:18:49,580
All set.

462
00:18:49,580 --> 00:18:50,340
Get them sorted.

463
00:18:53,940 --> 00:18:55,420
Do you have Sa's phone number?

464
00:18:55,900 --> 00:18:56,780
Sa

465
00:18:56,780 --> 00:18:59,260
only calls once a month.

466
00:18:59,500 --> 00:19:01,260
She said where she's working now

467
00:19:01,260 --> 00:19:02,340
is very inconvenient.

468
00:19:02,660 --> 00:19:03,380
So,

469
00:19:03,380 --> 00:19:05,060
none of us has her phone number.

470
00:19:05,060 --> 00:19:05,820
Yes.

471
00:19:06,180 --> 00:19:07,100
Our house

472
00:19:07,100 --> 00:19:08,380
is under Sa's name.

473
00:19:08,620 --> 00:19:10,660
An authorization letter is needed
if we want to sell it,

474
00:19:10,980 --> 00:19:12,940
so we had to turn to
Chi Cheung-wing for help.

475
00:19:15,900 --> 00:19:17,900
Keep an eye on what's going on
in the old town,

476
00:19:18,300 --> 00:19:19,620
especially that lawyer.

477
00:19:20,060 --> 00:19:21,620
Whatever she does is useless.

478
00:19:21,620 --> 00:19:23,780
Isn't the real land deed with you?

479
00:19:25,740 --> 00:19:26,460
A rare visitor.

480
00:19:28,020 --> 00:19:28,620
Mr. Chun,

481
00:19:28,780 --> 00:19:29,260
have a seat.

482
00:19:29,420 --> 00:19:29,900
Okay.

483
00:19:31,100 --> 00:19:32,460
I reached out plenty of times,

484
00:19:32,460 --> 00:19:33,540
but you kept saying you were busy.

485
00:19:34,340 --> 00:19:36,260
I really was tied up
with the land deed case.

486
00:19:36,900 --> 00:19:37,780
But it's all sorted now.

487
00:19:37,940 --> 00:19:38,660
Welcome.

488
00:19:38,980 --> 00:19:39,540
Waiter,

489
00:19:39,700 --> 00:19:40,380
add an extra set
of chopsticks and a bowl.

490
00:19:42,980 --> 00:19:43,580
Go ahead, you guys.

491
00:19:43,580 --> 00:19:44,100
I'll join you later.

492
00:19:44,100 --> 00:19:44,500
Alright.

493
00:19:46,860 --> 00:19:50,100
I never thought I'd be so honored

494
00:19:50,620 --> 00:19:53,260
to share a meal
with the president of the court.

495
00:19:54,660 --> 00:19:56,260
You're always like this.

496
00:19:56,540 --> 00:19:57,340
It's getting boring.

497
00:19:58,500 --> 00:19:59,900
Now I'm offering you a generous gift.

498
00:20:00,500 --> 00:20:01,580
Consider it compensation

499
00:20:01,580 --> 00:20:02,820
for the shot I fired at you.

500
00:20:05,380 --> 00:20:06,540
Trying to make peace?

501
00:20:07,020 --> 00:20:08,860
Before he died, Cho Wai-yi had
an insurance policy

502
00:20:09,180 --> 00:20:10,260
that I arranged for him,

503
00:20:10,780 --> 00:20:11,500
worth roughly

504
00:20:11,820 --> 00:20:12,740
over two million.

505
00:20:14,300 --> 00:20:15,700
Are you kidding?

506
00:20:16,540 --> 00:20:18,580
Are we going to dig up his body

507
00:20:18,580 --> 00:20:20,020
to get a death certificate?

508
00:20:20,020 --> 00:20:21,380
Me being the notary is enough.

509
00:20:23,540 --> 00:20:25,860
But his widow must sign it herself,

510
00:20:26,180 --> 00:20:27,540
because she is the sole beneficiary.

511
00:20:30,220 --> 00:20:31,900
Sa has to sign it herself?

512
00:20:34,820 --> 00:20:36,300
I haven't seen her in a long time.

513
00:20:36,300 --> 00:20:37,380
I don't know where she's gone.

514
00:20:38,580 --> 00:20:40,420
When her dad sold the house,

515
00:20:40,420 --> 00:20:41,500
didn't you give
the letter of authorization

516
00:20:41,820 --> 00:20:43,060
to him yourself?

517
00:20:47,020 --> 00:20:49,380
You're quite well-informed, aren't you?

518
00:20:51,260 --> 00:20:52,260
I did nothing.

519
00:20:53,180 --> 00:20:53,900
All I wish for

520
00:20:53,900 --> 00:20:55,700
is to see my son walk free,

521
00:20:55,900 --> 00:20:57,860
and finally live a simple life with him.

522
00:20:58,540 --> 00:20:59,500
I don't want to talk

523
00:21:00,380 --> 00:21:01,260
about the past anymore.

524
00:21:01,820 --> 00:21:02,580
Is that so?

525
00:21:06,860 --> 00:21:08,100
Two million.

526
00:21:08,100 --> 00:21:10,380
If I leave it,
the insurance company benefits.

527
00:21:13,180 --> 00:21:14,340
Can you help me save someone?

528
00:21:15,220 --> 00:21:15,900
What do you mean?

529
00:21:17,580 --> 00:21:18,660
Check this number.

530
00:21:18,660 --> 00:21:19,860
Where was it called from

531
00:21:19,860 --> 00:21:20,780
yesterday?

532
00:21:21,140 --> 00:21:22,860
Only the police have the authority

533
00:21:23,060 --> 00:21:24,980
to obtain data
from the telecoms company.

534
00:21:26,460 --> 00:21:27,100
Who do you want to save?

535
00:21:27,780 --> 00:21:29,380
Cho Wai-yi's wife and children.

536
00:21:33,660 --> 00:21:34,460
Over two million?

537
00:21:35,380 --> 00:21:36,140
You actually believe that?

538
00:21:36,260 --> 00:21:37,140
Don't you?

539
00:21:37,900 --> 00:21:39,060
Seriously?

540
00:21:39,580 --> 00:21:40,660
Do I look like an idiot?

541
00:21:41,180 --> 00:21:42,780
It's like he wants me dead all the time.

542
00:21:43,620 --> 00:21:44,540
That's true.

543
00:21:45,020 --> 00:21:45,860
However,

544
00:21:47,540 --> 00:21:49,340
he did say something right.

545
00:21:50,140 --> 00:21:51,860
Once the land deed case is done,

546
00:21:52,300 --> 00:21:53,660
it's payback time

547
00:21:53,980 --> 00:21:55,780
for all those old scores.

548
00:21:57,300 --> 00:21:59,140
It's not every day
he walks right into our hands.

549
00:22:04,420 --> 00:22:05,700
Based on telecoms records,

550
00:22:05,940 --> 00:22:07,220
the number was called

551
00:22:07,220 --> 00:22:07,980
from Pak Nai Island.

552
00:22:08,620 --> 00:22:10,540
If this is Chi Cheung-wing's hideout,

553
00:22:10,780 --> 00:22:11,780
we might find

554
00:22:11,780 --> 00:22:13,260
something unexpected there, Madam.

555
00:22:15,100 --> 00:22:16,740
It's Chi Cheung-wing's drug warehouse.

556
00:22:18,820 --> 00:22:19,740
Remember our first lesson

557
00:22:19,740 --> 00:22:20,820
in police college?

558
00:22:21,260 --> 00:22:21,940
What did it teach us?

559
00:22:22,900 --> 00:22:23,900
Is catching criminals more important,

560
00:22:24,340 --> 00:22:25,380
or saving lives?

561
00:22:25,940 --> 00:22:27,060
Saving lives, obviously.

562
00:22:27,900 --> 00:22:29,060
But the real issue is,

563
00:22:29,500 --> 00:22:30,460
can you trust Chun Yue?

564
00:22:30,820 --> 00:22:31,900
Not completely.

565
00:22:32,420 --> 00:22:34,140
I went to Yuen Sa's house too.

566
00:22:34,660 --> 00:22:35,940
Something felt off.

567
00:22:36,740 --> 00:22:38,180
So I asked someone else

568
00:22:38,460 --> 00:22:39,980
from the old town.

569
00:22:41,220 --> 00:22:43,140
Chi Cheung-wing
was just a small-timer back then.

570
00:22:43,540 --> 00:22:45,620
He and Cho Wai-yi both pursued Yuen Sa.

571
00:22:46,140 --> 00:22:47,620
But she chose

572
00:22:47,620 --> 00:22:48,980
Cho Wai-yi, who was a police officer.

573
00:22:48,980 --> 00:22:50,260
Chi Cheung-wing lost face.

574
00:22:50,260 --> 00:22:51,420
Of course he got mad.

575
00:22:52,020 --> 00:22:53,180
The old town has no secrets.

576
00:22:53,660 --> 00:22:54,460
Everyone knows about that.

577
00:22:57,300 --> 00:22:58,860
What I find most strange

578
00:22:59,700 --> 00:23:00,740
is Cho Wai-yi's death.

